        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 4:21PM EDT by NWS Indianapolis IN</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Shoals, or 24 miles southwest of Bedford, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shoals and Lacy.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
